Following the resignation of [[Robert Heaton Rhodes]] from his {{NZ electorate link|Akaroa}} seat in the New Zealand parliament, [[William Montgomery (New Zealand politician)|William Montgomery]] contested the 20 April 1874 by-election against [[Walter Pilliet]].  The results were 168 and 76 votes, respectively, ''i.e.'', a margin of 92 for Montgomery. He thus entered parliament during the [[5th New Zealand Parliament|5th]] term.<ref name="April 1874 Akaroa detailed results">{{Cite news|url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=search&d=TS18740421.2.9.2|title=GENERAL ASSEMBLY|issue=1912|date=21 April 1874|newspaper=The Star|accessdate=9 April 2010}}</ref>

